<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-070-135 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 337 057</DOCID><JOURNAL>IBM System User  Sept 1991 v12 n9 p44(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Tiny TC3. (Tiny Computers Ltd.'s microcomputer) (Hardware Review)(evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wheelwright, Geoff.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Tiny Computers Ltd's TC3 is a lightweight and small microcomputerthat is powerful for its size and attractively priced.andP;  The PCweighs 2.5 kilograms, measures 210mm long by 73mm high by 133mmwide, and still manages to possess power.andP;  For 499 poundssterling, the TC3 includes 1Mbyte of RAM, a 40Mbyte hard disk, a12MHz 80286 processor, a 3.5-inch 1.44Mbyte floppy disk drive, twoserial ports, one parallel port, a games controller port and avideo graphics array (VGA) display adaptor.andP;  Software includesDigital Research DR-DOS 5, a budget word processor and severalutility programs.andP;  There are no internal expansion slots but theproduct can connect to pocket Ethernet adaptors in its parallelport.andP;  The keyboard's space bar stuck on the test model, and thekeyboard is relatively small.andP;  A monochrome VGA display comes withthe TCS, but color monitors can be attached as well.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Tiny Computers Limited (Products).andO;Product:   Tiny Computers Tiny TC3 (Portable computer) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     Portable ComputersEvaluation.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Comparative ratings table. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>